WEBVTT

1
00:00:10.211 --> 00:00:12.580
<i>[rhythmic clapping]</i>

2
00:00:14.148 --> 00:00:15.583
Yeah.

3
00:00:15.649 --> 00:00:17.418
That's exactly
what you're doing.

4
00:00:17.485 --> 00:00:19.120
- It is.
- The airplane shot me down.

5
00:00:19.187 --> 00:00:20.954
- Yeah?
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

6
00:00:23.824 --> 00:00:26.394
Go around the back
and through the passage way.

7
00:00:26.460 --> 00:00:29.497
[cheering]

8
00:00:29.563 --> 00:00:32.933
Helen, June and Anita,
the Carter Family.

9
00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:35.936
[cheering]

10
00:00:40.641 --> 00:00:43.877
It's very nifty to be able
to entertain you

11
00:00:43.944 --> 00:00:45.446
a little bit today,

12
00:00:45.513 --> 00:00:47.515
and I don't know
what you're expecting,

13
00:00:47.581 --> 00:00:52.019
since we're all girls, and...
[laughter]

14
00:00:52.086 --> 00:00:54.322
Since we're the only girls
on the show,

15
00:00:54.388 --> 00:00:58.592
but I've got one announcement
to make before we do our part.

16
00:00:58.659 --> 00:01:00.961
This is as sexy
as I'm gonna get.

17
00:01:01.028 --> 00:01:03.964
[laughter]

18
00:01:04.031 --> 00:01:05.533
[whistles]

19
00:01:05.599 --> 00:01:07.235
No, this is
our little family,

20
00:01:07.301 --> 00:01:10.804
and we sing the songs mostly
of the old Carter family,

21
00:01:10.871 --> 00:01:13.174
and, well, we've been around
these parts for a long time,

22
00:01:13.241 --> 00:01:15.809
and we're proud to be part
of The Johnny Cash Show.

23
00:01:15.876 --> 00:01:18.412
We're gonna sing some new ones
and some old ones.

24
00:01:18.479 --> 00:01:20.381
So sit back, relax,
take your hands out

25
00:01:20.448 --> 00:01:22.015
of each other's pockets, and--

26
00:01:22.082 --> 00:01:23.251
[laughter]

27
00:01:23.317 --> 00:01:24.718
We'll sing a few little songs
for you,

28
00:01:24.785 --> 00:01:26.687
and then you'll see
who you've come to see.

29
00:01:26.754 --> 00:01:28.889
Old Golden Throat
will be right out.

30
00:01:28.956 --> 00:01:30.291
[laughter]

31
00:01:30.358 --> 00:01:31.525
<i>[Johnny Cash and June Carter's
"Jackson"]</i>

32
00:01:31.592 --> 00:01:34.662
<i>♪ Look out, Jackson town ♪</i>

33
00:01:34.728 --> 00:01:37.498
♪ Well, go on down to Jackson ♪

34
00:01:38.866 --> 00:01:42.102
<i>♪ Go ahead
and wreck your health ♪</i>

35
00:01:42.170 --> 00:01:45.706
♪ Go play your hand,
you big talking man ♪

36
00:01:45.773 --> 00:01:49.109
♪ And make a big fool
of yourself ♪

37
00:01:49.177 --> 00:01:51.979
♪ Yeah, go to Jackson ♪

38
00:01:52.045 --> 00:01:54.081
<i>I think for most people,
when they think about</i>

39
00:01:54.148 --> 00:01:55.516
<i>June Carter Cash,
they're probably thinking</i>

40
00:01:55.583 --> 00:01:57.017
about Reese Witherspoon.

41
00:01:57.084 --> 00:01:58.386
Will you marry me?

42
00:01:58.452 --> 00:01:59.620
<i>Because that film,
"Walk the Line,"</i>

43
00:01:59.687 --> 00:02:01.322
was really
June's mass exposure,

44
00:02:01.389 --> 00:02:02.790
I think, to a lot of people.

45
00:02:02.856 --> 00:02:05.293
<i>♪ Well, now we got married ♪</i>

46
00:02:05.359 --> 00:02:07.595
<i>Johnny Cash and June Carter.</i>

47
00:02:07.661 --> 00:02:09.797
<i>Johnny and June.</i>

48
00:02:09.863 --> 00:02:13.667
<i>"Walk the Line"
was the fairy tale.</i>

49
00:02:13.734 --> 00:02:17.037
The movie is about
a period of time about this big

50
00:02:17.104 --> 00:02:20.341
in a life so large.

51
00:02:20.408 --> 00:02:22.075
<i>♪ And that's a fact ♪</i>

52
00:02:22.142 --> 00:02:24.144
<i>It was probably gonna be
as much, if not more,</i>

53
00:02:24.212 --> 00:02:28.249
of June involved
in the equation than John.

54
00:02:28.316 --> 00:02:29.583
And I'll get shot
and killed here

55
00:02:29.650 --> 00:02:31.552
in Nashville for saying that.

56
00:02:31.619 --> 00:02:32.686
What would you like
to talk about?

57
00:02:32.753 --> 00:02:34.087
It really doesn't matter.

58
00:02:34.154 --> 00:02:35.823
I thought you might ask me
where Johnny was.

59
00:02:35.889 --> 00:02:38.192
- Where is Johnny?
- He's not here, is he?

60
00:02:38.259 --> 00:02:39.527
[laughter]

61
00:02:39.593 --> 00:02:41.128
<i>["Hello Stranger"]</i>

62
00:02:41.195 --> 00:02:44.532
♪ Well, hello stranger ♪

63
00:02:44.598 --> 00:02:47.735
If you only know
June Carter Cash,

64
00:02:47.801 --> 00:02:50.170
you're missing
a whole lot of things.

65
00:02:50.238 --> 00:02:52.206
<i>She was born
with one of the most</i>

66
00:02:52.273 --> 00:02:53.574
<i>famous names in country music.</i>

67
00:02:53.641 --> 00:02:55.042
<i>A remarkable
show business career.</i>

68
00:02:55.108 --> 00:02:57.511
Well, June Carter
was an incredible artist

69
00:02:57.578 --> 00:02:59.112
in her own right.

70
00:02:59.179 --> 00:03:00.781
<i>She's one
of the most charming</i>

71
00:03:00.848 --> 00:03:02.250
<i>and talented women
in country music today.</i>

72
00:03:02.316 --> 00:03:04.618
<i>A singer,
a comedienne, actress.</i>

73
00:03:04.685 --> 00:03:06.720
<i>♪ Let a working man
lay down ♪</i>

74
00:03:06.787 --> 00:03:08.656
♪ Yeah, I get a frown ♪

75
00:03:08.722 --> 00:03:11.024
<i>Who is June Carter Cash
to me?</i>

76
00:03:11.091 --> 00:03:14.828
Well, she's a badass bitch,
first off.

77
00:03:14.895 --> 00:03:18.532
You couldn't deny her.
she had that spark, the "it."

78
00:03:18.599 --> 00:03:19.833
You can't overdub the "it."

79
00:03:19.900 --> 00:03:21.101
♪ But I see you ♪

80
00:03:21.168 --> 00:03:22.503
But she's been married
so long to one man.

81
00:03:22.570 --> 00:03:24.738
No, no.
I had two before him.

82
00:03:24.805 --> 00:03:26.206
I put all mine together,
and I'm still

83
00:03:26.274 --> 00:03:27.608
not nearly caught up with you.

84
00:03:27.675 --> 00:03:29.076
[laughter]

85
00:03:29.142 --> 00:03:30.344
<i>♪ When your troubles
are like mine ♪</i>

86
00:03:30.411 --> 00:03:32.480
<i>There was so much
about my mother</i>

87
00:03:32.546 --> 00:03:33.914
<i>that may have been
misunderstood.</i>

88
00:03:33.981 --> 00:03:36.250
<i>Underrated and underappreciated.</i>

89
00:03:36.317 --> 00:03:37.885
<i>♪</i>

90
00:03:37.951 --> 00:03:40.153
<i>♪ So get up, rounder ♪</i>

91
00:03:40.220 --> 00:03:45.493
I think at the heart of it,
June's story hasn't been told.

92
00:03:45.559 --> 00:03:46.960
Would you welcome
June Carter Cash?

93
00:03:47.027 --> 00:03:49.363
<i>- June Carter Cash.
- June Carter Cash.</i>

94
00:03:49.430 --> 00:03:50.598
<i>June Carter Cash.</i>

95
00:03:50.664 --> 00:03:53.767
[cheers and applause]

96
00:04:04.512 --> 00:04:07.281
[birds chirping]

97
00:04:12.586 --> 00:04:14.688
- Hi.
- Everybody's here but Marty.

98
00:04:14.755 --> 00:04:16.023
Oh, they are?

99
00:04:16.089 --> 00:04:17.625
Well, you might know
Marty'd be late.

100
00:04:17.691 --> 00:04:19.159
It's part of what he does.

101
00:04:19.226 --> 00:04:22.363
Once you get to be a big star,
you're really late.

102
00:04:22.430 --> 00:04:24.432
I'm late because of Johnny.

103
00:04:24.498 --> 00:04:25.833
- Good morning.
- Hi, Miss June.

104
00:04:25.899 --> 00:04:26.800
- Good morning.
- Hi.

105
00:04:26.867 --> 00:04:28.101
Lord, look at everybody.

106
00:04:28.168 --> 00:04:29.837
It feels like old times.
- It does.

107
00:04:29.903 --> 00:04:31.339
It does, doesn't it?
How are you?

108
00:04:31.405 --> 00:04:34.308
<i>[soft acoustic music]</i>

109
00:04:34.375 --> 00:04:38.346
<i>♪</i>

110
00:04:38.412 --> 00:04:40.047
Well, here we are.

111
00:04:40.113 --> 00:04:43.617
- Hi, June.
- Come on in.

112
00:04:43.684 --> 00:04:45.786
I'm excited, everybody.

113
00:04:45.853 --> 00:04:50.157
I often wondered
how I'd ever do an album.

114
00:04:50.223 --> 00:04:52.560
And then I met
this really wonderful girl

115
00:04:52.626 --> 00:04:55.463
named Vicky Hamilton,
who was mostly

116
00:04:55.529 --> 00:04:57.297
in the world of rock and roll.

117
00:04:57.365 --> 00:05:00.133
There was an urgency
that she wanted

118
00:05:00.200 --> 00:05:03.437
to make this record.

119
00:05:03.504 --> 00:05:05.873
<i>So I had shopped it around</i>

120
00:05:05.939 --> 00:05:09.977
<i>to all
the major record companies,</i>

121
00:05:10.043 --> 00:05:12.580
and everybody passed.
I, like, couldn't believe it.

122
00:05:12.646 --> 00:05:13.914
There's no way
we're putting out

123
00:05:13.981 --> 00:05:18.486
a record with a 70-year-old
woman, you know?

124
00:05:18.552 --> 00:05:21.555
Four, five.

125
00:05:21.622 --> 00:05:24.358
<i>I was kind of incensed.</i>

126
00:05:24.425 --> 00:05:27.160
<i>This is, like,
country music royalty.</i>

127
00:05:27.227 --> 00:05:30.230
<i>How can you pass?</i>

128
00:05:30.297 --> 00:05:34.902
So I decided, OK, I'm gonna
start my own record company

129
00:05:34.968 --> 00:05:37.304
and raise the money
to make this record.

130
00:05:37.371 --> 00:05:40.273
I think I've changed
her whole life.

131
00:05:40.340 --> 00:05:43.577
So I'm hoping to make some
history again this morning.

132
00:05:43.644 --> 00:05:46.079
<i>♪</i>

133
00:05:46.146 --> 00:05:48.348
<i>That day,
we just gathered around</i>

134
00:05:48.416 --> 00:05:50.551
<i>to sing the songs
of her family,</i>

135
00:05:50.618 --> 00:05:52.019
my mom's family and things

136
00:05:52.085 --> 00:05:54.988
that she'd written down
through the years.

137
00:05:55.055 --> 00:05:57.357
I was looking for some
other good Carter family songs

138
00:05:57.425 --> 00:06:00.060
to sing on this album,
and "Diamonds in the Rough"

139
00:06:00.127 --> 00:06:02.062
is probably one
of my favorites, Marty.

140
00:06:02.129 --> 00:06:03.797
So why don't you and I sing it?

141
00:06:03.864 --> 00:06:05.198
You got it.

142
00:06:05.265 --> 00:06:08.168
["Diamonds in the Rough"]

143
00:06:08.235 --> 00:06:12.906
♪

144
00:06:12.973 --> 00:06:15.609
<i>My mother
was like a kid again.</i>

145
00:06:15.676 --> 00:06:17.745
<i>She was eager.</i>

146
00:06:17.811 --> 00:06:20.881
<i>It was as if she was ready</i>

147
00:06:20.948 --> 00:06:23.551
<i>to go get on a roller coaster.</i>

148
00:06:23.617 --> 00:06:28.822
♪ The day will soon be over ♪

149
00:06:28.889 --> 00:06:34.194
♪ And the digging
will be done ♪

150
00:06:34.261 --> 00:06:39.066
♪ No more gems be gathered ♪

151
00:06:39.132 --> 00:06:44.104
<i>♪ So let us all press on ♪</i>

152
00:06:44.171 --> 00:06:45.673
<i>I don't think
I've ever really known</i>

153
00:06:45.739 --> 00:06:49.409
<i>a life that's any different
than show business.</i>

154
00:06:49.477 --> 00:06:52.780
<i>My mother was Maybelle Carter,
who was a part</i>

155
00:06:52.846 --> 00:06:54.848
<i>of the original Carter family.</i>

156
00:06:54.915 --> 00:06:56.684
<i>This is my mama Maybelle,</i>

157
00:06:56.750 --> 00:07:00.488
<i>and then my aunt and my uncle,
Sara Carter, AP Carter.</i>

158
00:07:00.554 --> 00:07:03.791
<i>♪</i>

159
00:07:03.857 --> 00:07:08.729
<i>♪ The diamonds
will be shining ♪</i>

160
00:07:08.796 --> 00:07:14.367
<i>♪ No longer in the rough ♪</i>

161
00:07:14.434 --> 00:07:17.104
<i>♪</i>

162
00:07:17.170 --> 00:07:19.740
<i>At the time
that my mother was born,</i>

163
00:07:19.807 --> 00:07:22.843
<i>Maybelle had been recording
for a couple of years</i>

164
00:07:22.910 --> 00:07:24.545
with the
original Carter family.

165
00:07:24.612 --> 00:07:27.648
<i>[The Carter Family's
"Wildwood Flower"]</i>

166
00:07:27.715 --> 00:07:31.218
<i>♪</i>

167
00:07:31.284 --> 00:07:33.220
<i>One day, we found a man
that wanted us</i>

168
00:07:33.286 --> 00:07:35.422
<i>to come up and make a record.</i>

169
00:07:35.489 --> 00:07:38.592
So we went up to Bristol
and made our first record,

170
00:07:38.659 --> 00:07:42.496
and it's been going
ever since.

171
00:07:42.563 --> 00:07:45.866
<i>♪ Oh,
I'll twine with my mingles ♪</i>

172
00:07:45.933 --> 00:07:48.936
<i>♪ And waving black hair ♪</i>

173
00:07:49.002 --> 00:07:51.805
<i>The Carters, I mean,
they were the beginning.</i>

174
00:07:51.872 --> 00:07:56.009
<i>That was like the spontaneous
combustion of country music.</i>

175
00:07:56.076 --> 00:07:59.112
And June traces
right into that.

176
00:07:59.179 --> 00:08:01.448
<i>They had
so many tunes that formed</i>

177
00:08:01.515 --> 00:08:03.617
<i>a basis for our country
and western music</i>

178
00:08:03.684 --> 00:08:05.318
<i>as we know it today.</i>

179
00:08:05.385 --> 00:08:07.354
<i>And when people didn't know
what kind of a melody to use,</i>

180
00:08:07.420 --> 00:08:09.489
<i>they just went back
and grabbed</i>

181
00:08:09.557 --> 00:08:10.691
<i>an old Carter family melody</i>

182
00:08:10.758 --> 00:08:12.726
and hung on to that.

183
00:08:12.793 --> 00:08:14.662
<i>♪ I will dance ♪</i>

184
00:08:14.728 --> 00:08:15.996
<i>♪ I will sing ♪</i>

185
00:08:16.063 --> 00:08:19.667
♪ And my love shall be gay ♪

186
00:08:19.733 --> 00:08:22.102
♪ I will charm every heart ♪

187
00:08:22.169 --> 00:08:24.872
♪ And in his crown,
I will sway ♪

188
00:08:24.938 --> 00:08:26.506
<i>I just thought everybody had</i>

189
00:08:26.574 --> 00:08:28.041
<i>a Mother Maybelle Carter
that picked</i>

190
00:08:28.108 --> 00:08:29.943
<i>a "Wildwood Flower"
on the guitar.</i>

191
00:08:30.010 --> 00:08:31.712
<i>I didn't really know
she was different.</i>

192
00:08:31.779 --> 00:08:34.014
<i>♪</i>

193
00:08:34.081 --> 00:08:36.316
<i>Mother Maybelle was one
of the early</i>

194
00:08:36.383 --> 00:08:40.854
female guitar players
that actually slayed at guitar.

195
00:08:40.921 --> 00:08:42.756
Like,
she could straight up play.

196
00:08:42.823 --> 00:08:45.726
[rapid guitar playing]

197
00:08:45.793 --> 00:08:49.296
♪

198
00:08:49.362 --> 00:08:51.799
<i>My little fingers
were so calloused learning</i>

199
00:08:51.865 --> 00:08:53.333
<i>to play the "Wildwood Flower."</i>

200
00:08:53.400 --> 00:08:55.502
That was one of the first songs
I think

201
00:08:55.569 --> 00:08:57.304
that most country kids--
boys or girls--

202
00:08:57.370 --> 00:08:59.239
you want to play.
You know...

203
00:08:59.306 --> 00:09:01.241
♪ I will dance, I will sing ♪

204
00:09:01.308 --> 00:09:03.343
♪ And I'll play
the wildwood flower ♪

205
00:09:03.410 --> 00:09:08.415
<i>♪</i>

206
00:09:08.481 --> 00:09:10.483
<i>And my father was
instrumental in this, too--</i>

207
00:09:10.550 --> 00:09:11.919
<i>Ezra Carter.</i>

208
00:09:11.985 --> 00:09:14.554
<i>Daddy was a wonderful
influence in our life.</i>

209
00:09:14.622 --> 00:09:17.324
<i>Daddy was a brilliant man.</i>

210
00:09:17.390 --> 00:09:20.060
[engine revving]

211
00:09:20.127 --> 00:09:21.929
<i>♪</i>

212
00:09:21.995 --> 00:09:24.031
<i>She was very close to him.</i>

213
00:09:24.097 --> 00:09:27.300
<i>She'd ride
his motorcycle with him.</i>

214
00:09:27.367 --> 00:09:32.305
<i>She saw herself kind of
as a real rough and tumble</i>

215
00:09:32.372 --> 00:09:38.045
little kid, holding onto Daddy
as he drove his motorcycle

216
00:09:38.111 --> 00:09:40.447
<i>through that area.</i>

217
00:09:40.513 --> 00:09:43.583
<i>I think probably the lesson
that my father taught,</i>

218
00:09:43.651 --> 00:09:47.054
<i>the most important one,
was that we be ourselves.</i>

219
00:09:47.120 --> 00:09:48.656
<i>You develop what you have.</i>

220
00:09:48.722 --> 00:09:50.390
You do that as a person.

221
00:09:50.457 --> 00:09:53.593
<i>♪ Don't be a dirty miner
like me ♪</i>

222
00:09:53.661 --> 00:09:56.129
<i>When you grow up like that,
loving that place</i>

223
00:09:56.196 --> 00:09:57.497
<i>and knowing
that's who you are--</i>

224
00:09:57.564 --> 00:09:59.767
<i>when you just
become part of the woods</i>

225
00:09:59.833 --> 00:10:02.569
<i>and the bees and the birds,
and you're just</i>

226
00:10:02.636 --> 00:10:04.471
<i>a bunch of country little kids
running around</i>

227
00:10:04.537 --> 00:10:06.974
<i>and that's your place,
when you have to move away</i>

228
00:10:07.040 --> 00:10:09.009
in order to do
what you need to do,

229
00:10:09.076 --> 00:10:11.411
you carry that with you.

230
00:10:11.478 --> 00:10:13.613
<i>♪</i>

231
00:10:13.681 --> 00:10:16.583
<i>I'm sure you're enjoying
these good old songs</i>

232
00:10:16.650 --> 00:10:18.385
<i>as only the Carter Family
can sing them.</i>

233
00:10:18.451 --> 00:10:20.253
<i>Now here's the three
little Carter sisters,</i>

234
00:10:20.320 --> 00:10:21.488
<i>Helen, June, and Anita.</i>

235
00:10:21.554 --> 00:10:22.690
<i>And what's it gonna be?</i>

236
00:10:22.756 --> 00:10:23.691
<i>[together]
"In the Highway."</i>

237
00:10:23.757 --> 00:10:25.458
<i>"In the Highway."</i>

238
00:10:25.525 --> 00:10:30.263
<i>♪ In the highways,
in the hedges ♪</i>

239
00:10:30.330 --> 00:10:34.267
<i>My sisters Helen and Anita
and I went with my mother</i>

240
00:10:34.334 --> 00:10:36.837
<i>to the Texas border stations.</i>

