307
00:13:41.054 --> 00:13:43.223
<i>And so we went down and went</i>

308
00:13:43.290 --> 00:13:44.591
<i>to work at
"the Grand Ole Opry."</i>

309
00:13:44.657 --> 00:13:46.459
<i>♪</i>

310
00:13:46.526 --> 00:13:51.198
<i>♪ The Grand Ole Opry,
the Grand Ole Opry time ♪</i>

311
00:13:51.264 --> 00:13:54.167
[upbeat country music]

312
00:13:54.234 --> 00:13:58.438
♪

313
00:13:58.505 --> 00:14:01.174
♪ Do-si-do,
don't let them go ♪

314
00:14:01.241 --> 00:14:02.943
<i>If you were
going to Nashville,</i>

315
00:14:03.010 --> 00:14:05.345
<i>your dream was to be
on "The Grand Ole Opry,"</i>

316
00:14:05.412 --> 00:14:08.415
because everybody
all over the country

317
00:14:08.481 --> 00:14:10.217
listened to it
if you loved country music.

318
00:14:10.283 --> 00:14:13.921
♪

319
00:14:13.987 --> 00:14:16.924
<i>We've got the girl here who
can put an awful lot of humor</i>

320
00:14:16.990 --> 00:14:18.125
in any program.

321
00:14:18.191 --> 00:14:20.460
Let's make welcome
Miss June Carter.

322
00:14:20.527 --> 00:14:22.996
[cheers and applause]

323
00:14:23.063 --> 00:14:25.265
I'm gonna sing
if I can swaller

324
00:14:25.332 --> 00:14:26.799
before I get started 'cause

325
00:14:26.866 --> 00:14:28.101
this song ain't got
no swallerin' place.

326
00:14:28.168 --> 00:14:29.336
Let's try it.

327
00:14:29.402 --> 00:14:30.503
♪ I got a song ♪

328
00:14:30.570 --> 00:14:32.139
♪ It's a pretty good song ♪

329
00:14:32.205 --> 00:14:34.007
♪ Only one thing wrong
with the pretty good song ♪

330
00:14:34.074 --> 00:14:35.542
♪ 'Cause a pretty good song
goes along and along ♪

331
00:14:35.608 --> 00:14:37.410
<i>Back in those days,
Saturday night,</i>

332
00:14:37.477 --> 00:14:38.711
you'd turn on WSM Nashville
and listen

333
00:14:38.778 --> 00:14:40.147
to "The Grand Ole Opry."

334
00:14:40.213 --> 00:14:41.481
♪ Get along and along
and along and along ♪

335
00:14:41.548 --> 00:14:43.616
♪ Gonna get me
red in the face ♪

336
00:14:43.683 --> 00:14:47.054
<i>June Carter was
an all-around entertainer.</i>

337
00:14:47.120 --> 00:14:51.124
♪ 'Cause it ain't got
no swallerin place ♪

338
00:14:51.191 --> 00:14:53.961
<i>June Carter, here we are.</i>

339
00:14:54.027 --> 00:14:56.629
[cheers and applause]

340
00:14:56.696 --> 00:14:59.332
[screams]

341
00:14:59.399 --> 00:15:02.435
- What did I do?
- What did you do?

342
00:15:02.502 --> 00:15:04.504
You can quit throwing
that there--

343
00:15:04.571 --> 00:15:07.107
Well, if it ain't
June Carter.

344
00:15:07.174 --> 00:15:10.310
[applause]

345
00:15:12.245 --> 00:15:15.315
Of all
the knot-headed people,

346
00:15:15.382 --> 00:15:18.285
you are the knotty-headed
of knot-headed--

347
00:15:18.351 --> 00:15:20.187
well, bless his heart.

348
00:15:20.253 --> 00:15:22.956
It's Carl, that's who it is.

349
00:15:23.023 --> 00:15:24.958
Hello, Carl.
- Hello, June.

350
00:15:25.025 --> 00:15:27.727
- How you doing, old buddy?
- Pretty doggone good.

351
00:15:27.794 --> 00:15:29.362
<i>♪</i>

352
00:15:29.429 --> 00:15:33.900
♪ I thought I had seen
pretty girls in my time ♪

353
00:15:33.967 --> 00:15:39.439
♪ But that was
before I met you ♪

354
00:15:39.506 --> 00:15:42.209
<i>♪ I never saw one that I ♪</i>

355
00:15:42.275 --> 00:15:45.112
<i>Carl Smith
was the preeminent</i>

356
00:15:45.178 --> 00:15:48.015
<i>honky tonk singer of the day.</i>

357
00:15:48.081 --> 00:15:51.451
<i>He was a hot hunk,
one of the handsomest men</i>

358
00:15:51.518 --> 00:15:54.254
<i>in country music.</i>

359
00:15:54.321 --> 00:15:55.755
I heard what you
was saying out here.

360
00:15:55.822 --> 00:15:57.490
- What'd I say?
- You said--

361
00:15:57.557 --> 00:15:59.159
I didn't think you heard me.

362
00:15:59.226 --> 00:16:01.528
You said
you knowed me quite well.

363
00:16:01.594 --> 00:16:03.363
I just want you to know,
Carl,

364
00:16:03.430 --> 00:16:05.098
that I know you
quite well, too.

365
00:16:05.165 --> 00:16:07.134
- Oh.
- And I don't like--

366
00:16:07.200 --> 00:16:09.302
I don't like what I know.

367
00:16:09.369 --> 00:16:11.738
[laughter]

368
00:16:11.804 --> 00:16:13.273
No, I didn't--

369
00:16:13.340 --> 00:16:15.275
Hush, you're on television.
Look.

370
00:16:15.342 --> 00:16:19.012
[laughter]

371
00:16:19.079 --> 00:16:21.681
<i>♪ April and spring
is in the air ♪</i>

372
00:16:21.748 --> 00:16:25.752
<i>And June Carter
landed the star.</i>

373
00:16:25.818 --> 00:16:27.620
♪

374
00:16:27.687 --> 00:16:30.290
Of all the women
that wanted Carl,

375
00:16:30.357 --> 00:16:32.159
June is the one that got him.

376
00:16:32.225 --> 00:16:36.296
♪ I saw a little mugwump
sitting in a tree ♪

377
00:16:36.363 --> 00:16:37.930
<i>♪ Until he saw a female ♪</i>

378
00:16:37.997 --> 00:16:39.899
<i>They were the storybook
romance of the "Opry."</i>

379
00:16:39.966 --> 00:16:42.469
<i>They were like,
oh, June Carter</i>

380
00:16:42.535 --> 00:16:44.437
<i>of the famous Carter family,
and Carl Smith,</i>

381
00:16:44.504 --> 00:16:45.472
the biggest hit-maker
of the day.

382
00:16:45.538 --> 00:16:47.207
And you're like, "Wow."

383
00:16:47.274 --> 00:16:48.641
Perfect chemistry,
perfect timing,

384
00:16:48.708 --> 00:16:51.944
perfect everything--
they were, like, the couple.

385
00:16:52.011 --> 00:16:53.946
<i>♪</i>

386
00:16:54.013 --> 00:16:57.317
<i>There was a lot of joy,
a lot of laughter.</i>

387
00:16:57.384 --> 00:17:00.953
It sure had a beautiful outcome
with my sister Carlene.

388
00:17:01.020 --> 00:17:03.123
<i>♪</i>

389
00:17:03.190 --> 00:17:05.024
<i>♪ I'd let you know, June ♪</i>

390
00:17:05.092 --> 00:17:07.860
<i>See, Mama and Daddy looked
