391
00:17:07.927 --> 00:17:12.499
too, because they had
a very similar sense of humor,

392
00:17:12.565 --> 00:17:14.834
and they got a kick
out of each other.

393
00:17:14.901 --> 00:17:16.903
I'm kind of interested
in you, Carl Smith.

394
00:17:16.969 --> 00:17:19.239
You're quite a ladies man.
And I'm kind of--

395
00:17:19.306 --> 00:17:21.040
Is that right?
Well, all right.

396
00:17:21.108 --> 00:17:23.009
[laughter]

397
00:17:23.076 --> 00:17:25.078
I've got to--

398
00:17:25.145 --> 00:17:26.713
close your big mouth.

399
00:17:26.779 --> 00:17:28.047
Hey, no kidding.
I really am--

400
00:17:28.115 --> 00:17:30.917
You close yours.
I'm liable to fall in.

401
00:17:30.983 --> 00:17:33.220
Well, your big old ears
would hold you out.

402
00:17:33.286 --> 00:17:34.954
[laughter]

403
00:17:35.021 --> 00:17:38.591
<i>♪</i>

404
00:17:38.658 --> 00:17:41.694
]cheers and applause]

405
00:17:41.761 --> 00:17:44.664
<i>I'm gonna do it,
and I just need you to know--</i>

406
00:17:44.731 --> 00:17:47.567
<i>The character you did,
was it you? Or was it--</i>

407
00:17:47.634 --> 00:17:49.869
<i>No, it wasn't me.
I created her.</i>

408
00:17:49.936 --> 00:17:52.172
She would do almost anything
to get a laugh,

409
00:17:52.239 --> 00:17:55.708
and did, and I don't think
it was sincerely me.

410
00:17:55.775 --> 00:17:58.511
<i>No, it's just
a crazy little girl I played.</i>

411
00:17:58.578 --> 00:18:02.349
I just get up, and then
take the time to lay down.

412
00:18:02.415 --> 00:18:06.052
Life gets tedious, don't it?

413
00:18:06.119 --> 00:18:09.789
<i>Because she could
do it so well,</i>

414
00:18:09.856 --> 00:18:11.624
<i>people believed
that June Carter</i>

415
00:18:11.691 --> 00:18:17.630
<i>really was this uncouth hick.</i>

416
00:18:17.697 --> 00:18:20.467
<i>She made it seem effortless.</i>

417
00:18:20.533 --> 00:18:23.936
<i>It was not effortless.</i>

418
00:18:24.003 --> 00:18:29.376
<i>She had thick binders
