- Tell 'em what you done to me.

455
00:20:14.113 --> 00:20:15.615
<i>I was helping you, Carl.
I haven't--</i>

456
00:20:15.682 --> 00:20:16.616
<i>Yeah, you was helping me.</i>

457
00:20:16.683 --> 00:20:18.084
<i>Tell them what you done.</i>

458
00:20:18.150 --> 00:20:20.186
<i>I was just
helping you, old buddy.</i>

459
00:20:20.253 --> 00:20:21.621
You was in bad shape,

460
00:20:21.688 --> 00:20:23.523
and I was just giving you
a little, well--

461
00:20:23.590 --> 00:20:25.558
I tell you what.
I tell you what.

462
00:20:25.625 --> 00:20:28.528
He had a bad cold in his head.
- Yeah.

463
00:20:28.595 --> 00:20:32.765
<i>It's not something that you
really did in the mid-1950s.</i>

464
00:20:32.832 --> 00:20:36.569
<i>You really
didn't get divorced.</i>

465
00:20:36.636 --> 00:20:39.872
<i>But by 1955,</i>

466
00:20:39.939 --> 00:20:42.174
<i>and we're talking
less than three years,</i>

467
00:20:42.241 --> 00:20:43.810
they've already decided
they're going

468
00:20:43.876 --> 00:20:45.412
their separate ways...
- Right, I--

469
00:20:45.478 --> 00:20:47.514
You may be a good old girl,
but you don't look too good.

470
00:20:47.580 --> 00:20:49.682
- Oh, is that right?
- No, you don't.

471
00:20:49.749 --> 00:20:51.250
You ought to put some lipstick
on and bring your lips--

472
00:20:51.318 --> 00:20:53.520
<i>But they
still worked together...</i>

473
00:20:53.586 --> 00:20:55.121
<i>Around your eyes...</i>

