in her new Rolls-Royce

1386
01:02:19.904 --> 01:02:23.707
that John had just bought her,
left me with John.

1387
01:02:23.774 --> 01:02:25.442
I barely knew him.

1388
01:02:25.509 --> 01:02:28.412
So I had played some
of Ronnie's songs for them,

1389
01:02:28.478 --> 01:02:32.716
and she said, "Well,
I'm just gonna tell you,

1390
01:02:32.783 --> 01:02:34.451
he's pretty good."

1391
01:02:34.518 --> 01:02:37.054
And--
she goes like this...

1392
01:02:37.121 --> 01:02:38.422
[sucks teeth]

1393
01:02:38.488 --> 01:02:41.859
"He might have
a couple of hits.

1394
01:02:41.926 --> 01:02:43.327
He might."

1395
01:02:43.393 --> 01:02:46.296
And she goes, "Honey,

1396
01:02:46.363 --> 01:02:49.366
"I just need you to understand,

1397
01:02:49.433 --> 01:02:54.738
"It just seems like the ones
that really make it,

1398
01:02:54.805 --> 01:02:56.807
they're all a little crazy."

1399
01:02:56.874 --> 01:03:01.445
In other words don't do it.
You know, don't do it.

1400
01:03:01.511 --> 01:03:04.048
And Janine comes back
after a few hours,

1401
01:03:04.114 --> 01:03:06.183
and she was just kind of pale,
you know?

1402
01:03:06.250 --> 01:03:09.719
And I'm thinking, "Oh God,

1403
01:03:09.786 --> 01:03:11.822
she spent a lot
of money or what?"

1404
01:03:11.889 --> 01:03:15.392
No, it was that June had
read her the riot act about,

1405
01:03:15.459 --> 01:03:18.996
you know, dating a musician.

1406
01:03:19.063 --> 01:03:20.998
It was just funny.

1407
01:03:21.065 --> 01:03:23.100
She's right though.

1408
01:03:23.167 --> 01:03:25.870
They are.

1409
01:03:25.936 --> 01:03:27.371
[applause]

1410
01:03:27.437 --> 01:03:29.339
That's it,
ladies and gentlemen.

1411
01:03:29.406 --> 01:03:32.910
Thank you very much
and good night!

1412
01:03:32.977 --> 01:03:37.814
[cheers and applause]

1413
01:03:37.882 --> 01:03:42.519
<i>The rigors of the road
are difficult for a couple.</i>

1414
01:03:45.222 --> 01:03:50.560
<i>And when you work together
and live together, it's a lot.</i>

1415
01:03:50.627 --> 01:03:54.564
<i>Plus the constant glare
from the public</i>

1416
01:03:54.631 --> 01:03:57.667
and the projections on them
to live up

1417
01:03:57.734 --> 01:04:01.771
to some kind of myth, I mean,
that's almost impossible.

1418
01:04:01.838 --> 01:04:04.374
It was like a religion.

1419
01:04:04.441 --> 01:04:08.312
[cheers and applause]

1420
01:04:08.378 --> 01:04:10.380
I said, "I don't know
who this man is."

1421
01:04:10.447 --> 01:04:12.950
- Hello, I'm Johnny Cash.
- I know that.

1422
01:04:13.017 --> 01:04:16.720
Hello, I'm Johnny Cash.
Hello, I'm Johnny Cash.

1423
01:04:16.786 --> 01:04:18.855
<i>We had one of those
storybook kind of marriages</i>

1424
01:04:18.923 --> 01:04:21.391
<i>in the beginning
that just was unbelievable.</i>

1425
01:04:21.458 --> 01:04:23.327
<i>We had no problems
for the first 10,</i>

1426
01:04:23.393 --> 01:04:25.095
<i>12 years of our marriage.</i>

1427
01:04:25.162 --> 01:04:29.866
<i>I mean, it was like something
you would read about in books.</i>

1428
01:04:29.934 --> 01:04:31.801
<i>The first 10 years
they were together,</i>

1429
01:04:31.868 --> 01:04:35.605
<i>they were never apart
ever, ever.</i>

1430
01:04:35.672 --> 01:04:40.010
If she went shopping,
he went shopping with her.

1431
01:04:40.077 --> 01:04:42.879
<i>And I just was like,
"I would shoot myself."</i>

1432
01:04:42.947 --> 01:04:45.482
[laughs]

1433
01:04:45.549 --> 01:04:47.351
<i>The home I grew up in,</i>

1434
01:04:47.417 --> 01:04:49.453
<i>there was a beautiful
intimate relationship</i>

1435
01:04:49.519 --> 01:04:52.189
<i>that was going on.
My father was clean.</i>

1436
01:04:52.256 --> 01:04:54.524
He wasn't on anything
in the early 1970s.

1437
01:04:54.591 --> 01:04:56.994
<i>It was very peaceful</i>

1438
01:04:57.061 --> 01:05:00.664
<i>and very together as a unit</i>

1439
01:05:00.730 --> 01:05:03.533
<i>up until I was eight
or nine years old,</i>

1440
01:05:03.600 --> 01:05:08.005
<i>when their relationship
changed a great deal.</i>

1441
01:05:08.072 --> 01:05:11.675
<i>By 1980 or so,</i>

1442
01:05:11.741 --> 01:05:14.278
<i>my father rekindled
an addiction.</i>

1443
01:05:14.344 --> 01:05:16.546
<i>It would sneak up on him.</i>

1444
01:05:16.613 --> 01:05:19.616
<i>Something would trigger him,
or he'd get hurt,</i>

1445
01:05:19.683 --> 01:05:22.219
and you gave John
a bottle of anything

1446
01:05:22.286 --> 01:05:25.922
and didn't monitor him on it,
he's going to take it all.

1447
01:05:25.990 --> 01:05:30.160
June did not save my dad.

1448
01:05:30.227 --> 01:05:35.499
<i>You can't save another person
from their own addiction.</i>

1449
01:05:35.565 --> 01:05:37.734
Thank you very much.
I'd like to do my new record.

1450
01:05:37.801 --> 01:05:39.636
<i>♪ Bills, love, and pills ♪</i>

1451
01:05:39.703 --> 01:05:44.641
<i>♪ And drink,
and wine, and song ♪</i>

1452
01:05:44.708 --> 01:05:48.578
<i>June really struggled
to keep him looking good</i>

1453
01:05:48.645 --> 01:05:51.648
when he was in public,
you know, guarding him

1454
01:05:51.715 --> 01:05:54.084
from people
who might be disappointed

1455
01:05:54.151 --> 01:05:56.886
<i>if they saw him in that shape.</i>

1456
01:05:56.953 --> 01:05:59.856
<i>He chose to, you know,
just give himself to people.</i>

1457
01:05:59.923 --> 01:06:02.226
God bless you
and good night.

1458
01:06:02.292 --> 01:06:04.794
<i>♪ That's tired and gone ♪</i>

1459
01:06:04.861 --> 01:06:06.763
<i>There were a lot
of characters around him</i>

1460
01:06:06.830 --> 01:06:09.833
who were there
for the wrong reasons.

1461
01:06:09.899 --> 01:06:14.171
<i>June was kind,
but she could be ruthless.</i>

1462
01:06:14.238 --> 01:06:15.872
<i>It took a lot,</i>

1463
01:06:15.939 --> 01:06:20.010
but if it was clear
that you were not trustworthy,

1464
01:06:20.077 --> 01:06:21.511
she'd cut you out.

1465
01:06:21.578 --> 01:06:23.947
<i>[soft acoustic music]</i>

1466
01:06:24.014 --> 01:06:27.217
<i>Their relationship
suffered greatly.</i>

1467
01:06:27.284 --> 01:06:29.586
<i>They were fighting every day.</i>

1468
01:06:29.653 --> 01:06:31.921
<i>They were very angry
with each other,</i>

1469
01:06:31.988 --> 01:06:35.759
mostly my mom
angry with my father.

1470
01:06:35.825 --> 01:06:38.128
<i>I knew that they
were having trouble.</i>

1471
01:06:38.195 --> 01:06:40.364
<i>My mother, my sister, and I
were having lunch</i>

1472
01:06:40.430 --> 01:06:41.565
<i>at a restaurant in New York.</i>

1473
01:06:41.631 --> 01:06:43.300
<i>And she was there,</i>

1474
01:06:43.367 --> 01:06:47.671
and she said,
"There's a problem.

1475
01:06:47.737 --> 01:06:49.939
"Either he gets
straightened out

1476
01:06:50.006 --> 01:06:53.343
<i>or I have to leave,
and I don't want to leave."</i>

1477
01:06:53.410 --> 01:06:56.446
She just was at her wit's end.

1478
01:06:56.513 --> 01:06:58.348
So whatever happened,

1479
01:06:58.415 --> 01:07:00.184
it must have been
something horrible.

1480
01:07:00.250 --> 01:07:02.719
<i>♪</i>

1481
01:07:02.786 --> 01:07:05.389
<i>I was traveling with them,</i>

1482
01:07:05.455 --> 01:07:07.457
<i>and, you know,
I remember one night</i>

1483
01:07:07.524 --> 01:07:11.027
hearing my dad's breathing
being very labored.

1484
01:07:12.629 --> 01:07:14.464
<i>He would breathe
all the way out,</i>

1485
01:07:14.531 --> 01:07:17.067
<i>and then
his breath would stop,</i>

1486
01:07:17.134 --> 01:07:18.968
<i>and then after
a little bit, he'd...</i>

1487
01:07:19.035 --> 01:07:20.204
[sniffs, gasps]

1488
01:07:20.270 --> 01:07:21.805
and he'd start breathing again.

1489
01:07:21.871 --> 01:07:25.909
Well, at one point, it stopped,
and he didn't start back.

1490
01:07:29.079 --> 01:07:32.682
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

1491
01:07:32.749 --> 01:07:36.120
<i>Scenes of my life
passed before my eyes.</i>

1492
01:07:36.186 --> 01:07:38.222
<i>I saw myself at my peaks</i>

1493
01:07:38.288 --> 01:07:41.858
<i>and I saw myself walk through
my deepest, darkest valleys.</i>

1494
01:07:41.925 --> 01:07:44.461
<i>♪</i>

1495
01:07:44.528 --> 01:07:46.696
<i>I ran in,
and I got my mother,</i>

1496
01:07:46.763 --> 01:07:49.699
<i>and we got him up,
and we put him in the bathtub,</i>

1497
01:07:49.766 --> 01:07:53.270
<i>and we poured water
all over him.</i>

1498
01:07:53.337 --> 01:07:55.739
I remember he woke up,

1499
01:07:55.805 --> 01:07:59.543
and he was very incoherent.

1500
01:07:59.609 --> 01:08:02.879
<i>I was afraid.
I was overwhelmed.</i>

1501
01:08:02.946 --> 01:08:06.283
<i>I was crying my eyes out.
I mean, I was a kid, you know?</i>

1502
01:08:06.350 --> 01:08:12.322
But it wasn't long after that
many changes began to occur.

1503
01:08:12.389 --> 01:08:15.091
<i>♪ There was a time ♪</i>

1504
01:08:15.159 --> 01:08:18.428
<i>There was an intervention.
We had an intervention.</i>

1505
01:08:18.495 --> 01:08:21.631
<i>We all wrote letters
to my dad.</i>

1506
01:08:21.698 --> 01:08:23.467
<i>It was very hard
for me to do that.</i>

1507
01:08:23.533 --> 01:08:24.934
<i>We read them all to my father,</i>

1508
01:08:25.001 --> 01:08:26.536
<i>and he agreed
to go to treatment</i>

1509
01:08:26.603 --> 01:08:27.771
at Betty Ford Center.

1510
01:08:27.837 --> 01:08:30.740
<i>[tender country music]</i>

1511
01:08:30.807 --> 01:08:33.243
<i>When I saw him again
in California,</i>

1512
01:08:33.310 --> 01:08:37.113
<i>that person was back,
my old dad was back again.</i>

1513
01:08:37.181 --> 01:08:39.983
♪ Hey Willy Wallacky,
hey John Dougal-y ♪

1514
01:08:40.049 --> 01:08:44.354
♪ A lane, quo'Rushity,
noo, noo, noo ♪

1515
01:08:44.421 --> 01:08:46.656
<i>♪</i>

1516
01:08:46.723 --> 01:08:50.394
♪ Have I told you lately ♪

1517
01:08:50.460 --> 01:08:53.197
♪ That I love you? ♪

1518
01:08:53.263 --> 01:08:57.334
<i>And at that point, there was
a great forgiveness in place.</i>

1519
01:08:57.401 --> 01:09:00.970
You know, my mother was like,
"It's hard to be Johnny Cash."

1520
01:09:01.037 --> 01:09:04.107
It's like,
"How did she forgive him?"

1521
01:09:04.174 --> 01:09:06.476
<i>She had a way of forgiving</i>

1522
01:09:06.543 --> 01:09:08.645
<i>as if it was
from East to West.</i>

1523
01:09:08.712 --> 01:09:12.449
<i>♪</i>

1524
01:09:12.516 --> 01:09:15.619
[cheers and applause]

1525
01:09:17.421 --> 01:09:18.722
<i>And maybe a lot of times,</i>

1526
01:09:18.788 --> 01:09:21.691
they did buy into
their own myth,

1527
01:09:21.758 --> 01:09:23.327
for better or for worse.

1528
01:09:23.393 --> 01:09:25.195
Maybe that kept them going
at a time

1529
01:09:25.262 --> 01:09:26.863
when they could have broken up.

1530
01:09:26.930 --> 01:09:28.998
You know, it's like, well,
we have this thing together

1531
01:09:29.065 --> 01:09:31.368
that's bigger than us.

1532
01:09:31.435 --> 01:09:33.036
I mean, that's what
it looked like

1533
01:09:33.102 --> 01:09:35.939
<i>from the outside,
and you never know</i>

1534
01:09:36.005 --> 01:09:38.642
<i>what goes on
in people's marriages anyway.</i>

1535
01:09:41.545 --> 01:09:43.780
[light strumming]

1536
01:09:43.847 --> 01:09:45.882
<i>It's real easy.</i>

1537
01:09:45.949 --> 01:09:47.717
I don't know if you can
learn it fast enough or not,

1538
01:09:47.784 --> 01:09:49.819
but we might
could get it down.

1539
01:09:49.886 --> 01:09:52.956
It's one I wrote just
before I sent them to Vicky.

1540
01:09:53.022 --> 01:09:56.360
It's...
- "Wings of Angels."

1541
01:09:56.426 --> 01:09:59.663
<i>♪ Bare me up
on wings of angels ♪</i>

1542
01:09:59.729 --> 01:10:02.832
<i>♪ Let me hear
the choir sing ♪</i>

1543
01:10:02.899 --> 01:10:06.570
♪ Let me see the faces ♪

1544
01:10:06.636 --> 01:10:09.939
♪ Of the cherubim ♪

1545
01:10:10.006 --> 01:10:11.675
♪

1546
01:10:11.741 --> 01:10:14.244
<i>♪ Lift me up
on wings of angels ♪</i>

1547
01:10:14.311 --> 01:10:17.981
<i>I was in the lobby
at the Betty Ford Center.</i>

1548
01:10:18.047 --> 01:10:22.686
<i>We went back there to visit
them, and John was in rehab.</i>

1549
01:10:22.752 --> 01:10:27.891
And June was
at the codependency center.

1550
01:10:27.957 --> 01:10:30.427
<i>♪ Jesus, I'm trying ♪</i>

1551
01:10:30.494 --> 01:10:32.962
<i>♪ To get to you ♪</i>

1552
01:10:33.029 --> 01:10:34.898
<i>When she went
into Betty Ford Center,</i>

1553
01:10:34.964 --> 01:10:36.800
<i>there was an education
that happened</i>

1554
01:10:36.866 --> 01:10:39.869
in her life of what
codependency is that she

1555
01:10:39.936 --> 01:10:42.372
had never conceived of before.

1556
01:10:42.439 --> 01:10:45.442
<i>She said to me,
"Oh, honey, I just learned</i>

1557
01:10:45.509 --> 01:10:48.678
I'm going to die before John."

1558
01:10:48.745 --> 01:10:50.013
I said, "Why?"

1559
01:10:50.079 --> 01:10:51.648
She goes,
"Well, because codependency

1560
01:10:51.715 --> 01:10:53.182
"is really, really hard.

1561
01:10:53.249 --> 01:10:54.884
We become super parents."

1562
01:10:54.951 --> 01:10:56.686
And I said, "Well,
what do you do in the unit?"

1563
01:10:56.753 --> 01:10:59.255
And she goes, "We paint.
We play with clay.

1564
01:10:59.323 --> 01:11:02.826
"We fly kites.
We learn to be kids again.

1565
01:11:02.892 --> 01:11:04.728
<i>"And I'm telling you this
because you</i>

1566
01:11:04.794 --> 01:11:07.364
<i>need to know this."</i>

1567
01:11:07.431 --> 01:11:09.933
<i>Being codependent,
which means sometimes</i>

1568
01:11:09.999 --> 01:11:12.436
you're too good
for your own good,

1569
01:11:12.502 --> 01:11:16.005
where you put others

1570
01:11:16.072 --> 01:11:19.108
<i>too much ahead
of your own needs.</i>

1571
01:11:19.175 --> 01:11:21.177
<i>You helped him to heal
a lot of those scars.</i>

1572
01:11:21.244 --> 01:11:24.047
<i>Well, that would be nice
if I could say I did that.</i>

1573
01:11:24.113 --> 01:11:26.416
I think all of us girls would
like to be able to claim

1574
01:11:26.483 --> 01:11:28.017
that we healed our husbands.

1575
01:11:28.084 --> 01:11:30.253
You know, if it doesn't work,
you just pop them in the head

1576
01:11:30.320 --> 01:11:32.121
and holler "heal."

1577
01:11:32.188 --> 01:11:34.624
<i>[laughter]
It doesn't work.</i>

1578
01:11:34.691 --> 01:11:36.292
<i>You sound like
you kind of regret some</i>

1579
01:11:36.360 --> 01:11:39.663
<i>of the things that go along
with the status</i>

1580
01:11:39.729 --> 01:11:41.565
you've achieved
in the business.

1581
01:11:41.631 --> 01:11:43.667
Oh, I don't
regret any of that.

1582
01:11:43.733 --> 01:11:46.436
There is pain
in everybody's life.

1583
01:11:46.503 --> 01:11:48.738
<i>It's something we all
are confronted with.</i>

1584
01:11:48.805 --> 01:11:50.507
<i>Every one of us has pain.</i>

1585
01:11:50.574 --> 01:11:51.941
<i>It helps us, you know?</i>

1586
01:11:52.008 --> 01:11:54.110
If you've put it behind you,
boy, it'll push you.

1587
01:11:54.177 --> 01:11:56.513
It'll stick you right
through the rest of the world

1588
01:11:56.580 --> 01:11:58.247
if you'll stick it behind you.

1589
01:11:58.314 --> 01:12:00.384
Don't let it hang with you.
Don't put it in front of you.

1590
01:12:00.450 --> 01:12:02.419
That's what I say.

1591
01:12:02.486 --> 01:12:05.422
[cheers and applause]

1592
01:12:05.489 --> 01:12:08.392
[bright acoustic music]

1593
01:12:08.458 --> 01:12:11.595
♪

1594
01:12:16.433 --> 01:12:22.338
<i>There comes a point
in every entertainer's life,</i>

1595
01:12:22.406 --> 01:12:24.374
<i>you're faced
with the mortality,</i>

1596
01:12:24.441 --> 01:12:27.977
your own, and the mortality
of your career.

1597
01:12:28.044 --> 01:12:31.948
And it happened
to John and June.

1598
01:12:32.015 --> 01:12:33.950
<i>In the early 1980s,
my father didn't</i>

1599
01:12:34.017 --> 01:12:36.119
<i>have very many hits at all.</i>

1600
01:12:36.185 --> 01:12:41.625
And 1984, after he sort of
picked back up his life again,

1601
01:12:41.691 --> 01:12:43.059
it was actually--
he was actually dropped

1602
01:12:43.126 --> 01:12:45.862
by his record label
at the time.

1603
01:12:45.929 --> 01:12:48.532
<i>It was a dramatic slowdown.</i>

1604
01:12:48.598 --> 01:12:51.267
<i>You know, I saw Johnny
and June the first time</i>

1605
01:12:51.334 --> 01:12:53.670
playing
for 16,000 screaming fans.

1606
01:12:53.737 --> 01:12:55.805
And then the '80s,
we would sometimes

1607
01:12:55.872 --> 01:12:58.174
<i>go to clubs with 300 people.</i>

1608
01:12:58.241 --> 01:13:01.478
<i>They'd been the biggest
stars in the world</i>

1609
01:13:01.545 --> 01:13:03.346
for six, eight, ten--

1610
01:13:03.413 --> 01:13:09.218
and then it started
not being that way.

1611
01:13:09.285 --> 01:13:10.954
- Good night.
- Good night.

1612
01:13:11.020 --> 01:13:14.190
<i>I think June was
unsettled by that.</i>

1613
